William Henry CHAPMAN v. C. H. LOONEY, Warden, U. S. Penitentiary, Leavenworth, Kansas, et al. No. 5226. United States Court of Appeals Tenth Circuit. Sept. 12, 1955. Appeal from the United States District Court for the District of Kansas. No appearance for appellant. William C. Farmer, U. S. Atty., and Milton P. Beach, Asst. U. S. Atty., Topeka, Kan., for appellees.

Before PHILLIPS, Chief Judge, and HUXMAN, Circuit Judge.

PER CURIAM.

Docketed and dismissed, on motion of appellee, C. H. Looney, Warden, U. S. Penitentiary, Leavenworth, Kansas, on ground appeal is moot.
